Klondike Wind Power LLC FERC ELECTRIC TARIFF NO. 1
1. Availability: Klondike Wind Power LLC, an Oregon limited liability company ("Klondike Wind Power"), makes electric energy and capacity available under this Tariff to any purchaser for resale. Klondike Wind Power also makes available, to any purchaser, ancillary services except as prohibited below: a. PJM: Klondike Wind Power offers regulation and frequency response service, energy imbalance service and operating reserve service (which includes spinning, 10-minute reserves, and 30-minute reserves) for sale into the market administered by PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM") and, where the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff permits, the self-supply of these services to purchasers for a bilateral sale that is used to satisfy the ancillary services requirements of the PJM Office of Interconnection. b. New York: Klondike Wind Power offers regulation and frequency response service, and operating reserve service (which includes 10-minute non-synchronous, 30-minute operating reserves, 10-minute spinning reserves, and 10-minute non-spinning reserves) for sale to purchasers in the market administered by the New York Independent System Operator, Inc. c. New England: Klondike Wind Power offers regulation and frequency response service (automatic generator control), operating reserve service (which includes 10-minute spinning reserve, 10-minute non-spinning reserve, and 30-minute operating reserve service) to purchasers within the markets administered by the ISO New England, Inc. d. California: Klondike Wind Power offers regulation service, spinning reserve service, and non-spinning reserve service to the California Independent System Operator Corporation ("CAISO") and to others that are self-supplying ancillary services to the CAISO. Klondike Wind Power is authorized to transact at market-based rates in the Energy Imbalance Market administered by the CAISO. Avangrid Renewables, LLC, et al., 182 FERC 61,193 (March 24, 2023). e. MISO. Klondike Wind Power offers regulation service and operating reserve service (which include 10-minute spinning reserve and 10-minute supplemental reserve) for sale to the Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc. ("MISO") and to others that are self-supplying ancillary services to MISO. f. Southwest Power Pool. Klondike Wind Power offers regulation service and operating reserve service (which include 10-minute spinning reserve and 10-minute supplemental reserve) for sale to the Southwest Power Pool, Inc. ("SPP") and to others that are self-supplying ancillary services to SPP. g. Third Party Ancillary Services. Klondike Wind Power offers Regulation Service, Reactive Supply and Voltage Control Service, Energy and Generator Imbalance Service, Operating Reserve-Spinning, Operating Reserve-Supplemental, and Primary Frequency Response Service. Sales will not include the following: (1) sales to an RTO or an ISO, i.e., where that entity has no ability to self-supply ancillary services but instead depends on third parties; and (2) sales to a traditional, franchised public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier, or sales where the underlying transmission service is on the system of the public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier. Sales of Operating Reserve-Spinning and Operating Reserve-Supplemental will not include sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers, except where the Commission has granted authorization. Sales of Regulation Service and Reactive Supply and Voltage Control Service will not include sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers, except at rates not to exceed the buying public utility transmission provider's OATT rate for the same service or where the Commission has granted authorization. 2. Applicability: This Tariff is applicable to all sales of electric energy and capacity by Klondike Wind Power not otherwise subject to a particular tariff of Klondike Wind Power. 3. Rates: All sales shall be made at rates established by agreement between the purchaser and Klondike Wind Power. 4. Other Terms and Conditions: All other terms and conditions shall be established by agreement between the purchaser and Klondike Wind Power. 5. Compliance with Commission Regulations: Klondike Wind Power shall comply with the provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning Klondike Wind Power's market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes Klondike Wind Power to engage in affiliate sales under this tariff or otherwise restricts or limits the Klondike Wind Power's market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with applicable provisions of 18 C.F.R. part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning Klondike Wind Power's market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this tariff. 6. Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority: In PPM One LLC, Letter Order, Docket No. ER97-3886-000 (Sept. 10, 1997), Klondike Wind Power received (i) waiver the accounting and reporting requirements contained in 18 C.F.R. Parts 41, 101, and 141; (ii) waiver of 18 C.F.R. part 35, Subparts B and C, except for sections 35.12(a), 35.13(b), 35.15, and 35.16; and (iii) blanket approval under Part 34. 7. Seller Category: Klondike Wind Power is a Category 1 Seller, as defined in 18 C.F.R. 35.36(a), in the Northeast, Central, Southeast and Southwest Regions and in the Southwest Power Pool. Klondike Wind Power is a Category 2 Seller, as defined in 18 C.F.R. 35.36(a), in the Northwest Region. 8. Effective Date: This tariff is effective upon the date specified by the Commission.
